OL,6,FToday Liverpool has become a sanctuary
OL,7,Ffor lost souls, seeking shelter and
OL,8,Fsafety. More asylum seekers live in
OL,9,FLiverpool than almost any other area
OL,10,Fof Britain.
OL,12,FArriving in the city with next to
OL,13,Fnothing, usually sent up from the
OL,14,Fsouth of England by Home Office
OL,15,Fcontractors, for many asylum seekers
OL,16,FSt Anne's church just outside of the
OL,17,Fcity centre is one of the first places
OL,18,Fthey visit.
